cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper primarily focuses on the security aspect of autonomous cars and proposes a novel intrusion detection system using machine learning models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models for extracting road contexts from sensory information, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for implementing the proposed system also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of camera images, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves the use of control signals for maneuvering the car, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
